By: Abu ’l-Qâsim al-'Irâqî
---
Hermes Trismegistus said： ‘O Sages! Consider the red which is perfect and
that which is imperfect, and the perfect yellow and that which is imperfect,
and the black which is perfect and that which is imperfect-each one of these
is from one root.’
